  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Trauma Healing w/ 60 Youth Leaders in South Sudan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Many youth in South Sudan have grown up surrounded by war, thereby developing a mistrust of others and increased fear &amp; anger. These conditions too often lead to retaliation- perpetuating cycles of hurt &amp; violence. This project will work with 60 youth leaders from 2 warring tribes in Bor &amp; Pibor. Our comprehensive approach includes arts, theater, &amp; storytelling to reduce the harmful effects of trauma, interrupt cycles of violence, and increase reconciliation, empathy, leadership, &amp; connection.</narrative>
  </description>
